ically Hip’s farewell concert, the Truth and Reconciliation Commission, and ongoing Black equality struggles. Each day represents a window on contemporary Canada, jumpstarting reflection and conversation about who we are as a nation and how we got here. Ten Days That Shaped Modern Canada is the perfect guide for all those curious about the forces that shape our country and about how we understand our place in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aCreative Writing / Literary Nonfiction. 4aCreative Writing. 4aHistory / Canadian History. 4aHistory. 4aPolitical Science / Canadian Politics. 4aPolitical Science. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh  aCanadian Constitution.  aCanadian politics.  aEgan.  aGord Downie.  aHockey.  aMulticulturalism Act.  aOctober Crisis.  aQuebec Referendum.  aTRC.  aTeam Canada.  aThe Tragically Hip.  aViola Desmond.  aconcise.  aevents.  agay marriage.  asame sex marriage.  asignificant dates.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212663140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772126631423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772126631/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles